## ğŸš€ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/sumit-TGT/sustainability-dashboard.git
cd sustainability-dashboard

2. Install dependencies

cd backend
npm install

3.  Configure environment variables
Create a .env file inside /backend:

PORT=3000
DB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/esg-dashboard
POWER_BI_WORKSPACE_ID=your_workspace_id
POWER_BI_REPORT_ID=your_report_id
POWER_BI_EMBED_URL=https://app.powerbi.com/reportEmbed?reportId=your_report_id&groupId=your_group_id
POWER_BI_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token


4. Start the backend server
node app.js

ğŸ§ª API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint                      | Description                  |
| ------ | ----------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `POST` | `/api/v1/esg/upload`          | Upload ESG data              |
| `GET`  | `/api/v1/esg/:tenantId`       | Get ESG data by tenant       |
| `GET`  | `/api/v1/esg/:tenantId/pdf`   | Download ESG report as PDF   |
| `GET`  | `/api/v1/esg/:tenantId/excel` | Download ESG report as Excel |
| `GET`  | `/api/v1/mapping`             | Get ESG â†’ SDG mapping data   |


ğŸ“Š Dashboards
Power BI

Embed HTML file in dashboard/power-bi/index.html

Set report ID, embed URL, and access token from .env

Grafana

Use .json dashboards inside dashboard/grafana-config/

Configure Grafana to use MongoDB or InfluxDB (via proxy if needed)


